cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to represent and classify semantic relations between words. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses supervised machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
